# Premium offer button

For opt-in incentive buttons — "I want 5% off", "Add gift wrap", bonus/upgrade
offers — use the shared **`.btn-premium-offer`** class instead of a one-off green
or flat button.

```tsx
<button type="button" className="btn-premium-offer" onClick={onApplyOffer}>
  {label}
</button>
```

## What it gives you

- Gold gradient (`--accent-secondary` → `--accent`) with dark brand text
  (`--accent-cta-text`), a soft gold border, and an inner highlight — reads as a
  premium chip beside the dark `--primary` pay button without stealing its emphasis.
- A slow shimmer sweep (~3.2s) to draw the eye gently.
- Lift-on-hover / press-on-active feedback.
- Respects `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` (shimmer + transitions disabled).

## Where it lives

- Styles: `app/globals.css` (`.btn-premium-offer`, `@keyframes btn-premium-offer-shimmer`).
- Origin / reference usage: cart discount button in `app/[lang]/cart/CartCheckoutView.tsx`.

## Notes

- Keep the primary action on `--primary` (dark). The offer button is secondary.
- Do not recolor to green/blue per-instance — adjust the shared class or the
  `--accent*` tokens so all offer buttons stay consistent.
- Add layout (width, exit animation, spacing) at the call site; the class only
  owns the visual "offer" look.
